peopleAlsoAsk.question: What is the holy grail of postage?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: The British Guiana 1-cent magenta postage stamp is known by many stamp collectors and philatelists as the world's most famous stamp. It is considered a rare stamp that was issued in British Guiana (known today as Guyana) during 1856 in very limited numbers. It is the only one stamp known to exist today.
